<HEADLINE>
FT  01 JUN 92 / Construction Contracts: Barratt busy in Scotland
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BARRATT CONSTRUCTION
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
the Scottish-based construction arm of Barratt Developments - has been
awarded new contracts worth in excess of Pounds 5m.
In Edinburgh, work will begin shortly on a Pounds 2m contract at the former
Scottish &amp; Newcastle Maltings on Slateford Road for its housebuilding sister
company, Barratt Scotland. In addition to building a six-storey block of 36
apartments, Barratt Construction will carry out the demolition and facade
retention of the two Victorian B-listed maltings buildings, where a further
114 new flats are planned.
Work has already begun on a Pounds 1.6m design and build contract in Dundee
for rented housing specialist Quality Street, constructing a range of 42
apartments in Abercorn Street.
In the North East, the company has secured new business worth more than
Pounds 1.5m, including a development of 27 flats for Langstane Housing
Association at Great Northern Road, Aberdeen.
Additional projects scheduled to begin shortly include the fitting out of
offices in Albyn Place for Coopers &amp; Lybrand Deloitte, and a new residence
for private clients at Birchbank, near Kemnay.
</TEXT>
