<HEADLINE>
FT  01 JUN 92 / Construction Contracts: Pounds 24m orders awarded to Hall &amp;
Tawse
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
HALL &amp; TAWSE, the construction division of Raine Industries, has been
awarded Pounds 24m worth of contracts.
Nottingham-based Hall &amp; Tawse Eastern has won a Pounds 2.7m contract to
construct a two-storey science and technology building at Derbyshire College
of Higher Education - plus a Pounds 1.6m contract to build a research centre
in Loughborough for British Gas.
Hall &amp; Tawse Scotland has secured two contracts totalling Pounds 3.1m to
fit-out Marks &amp; Spencer stores in Paisley and Inverness.
A 69-bed hospital is being constructed in Reading by Hall &amp; Tawse Southern
for Independent British Hospitals at a cost of Pounds 2.7m.
The Stourbridge-based Hall &amp; Tawse Western has been awarded refurbishment
contracts for Pounds 600,000 with the West Midlands Police Authority, and
for Pounds 400,000 with Birmingham City Council, to upgrade Cockshut Hill
School in Yardley.
Hall &amp; Tawse Partnership, the social housing specialist, has won a Pounds 1m
contract from Redland Housing Association, to design and build 25 dwellings
in the Avon village of Camerton.
</TEXT>
