<HEADLINE>
FT  30 MAY 92 / MFI breached consumer law
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MFI, THE furniture retailer, was yesterday convicted of falsely claiming it
was reducing the price of its stock.
MFI Furniture Centres denied at Swansea magistrates' court nine breaches of
consumer protection legislation, but was convicted on all counts. The
company was fined Pounds 2,000 on each count and ordered to pay Pounds 8,970
costs.
Mr Neil Palfreeman, MFI marketing director, admitted that at a store at
Llansamlet, Swansea, a suite priced at Pounds 1,289.99 was given a 30 per
cent discount, but told the court: 'It was never sold at that pre-sale
price.'
