<TEXT>
World airline passenger traffic will recover quickly over the next three
years after a setback in 1991, the International Civil Aviation Organisation
(ICAO) said yesterday, writes Daniel Green. ICAO predicted annual growth of
more than 10 per cent in the Asia-Pacific region, by 1994, while growth in
Europe was likely to remain below 2 per cent a year. The agency estimated
that average world growth in 1992 would be 4.2 per cent, rising to 5.3 per
cent in 1993 and 6.4 per cent in 1994.
