FT  30 MAY 92 / Briefcase, Q&amp;A: Minor stakes
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
I AM forming a small limited company with a friend. We wish to issue some of
the shares to our minor children. Is this possible without unusual
formality? We wish to avoid complicated and expensive legal procedures.
There is no restriction on minors owning shares in a limited company: you
can issue shares to the children in the normal way.
