<HEADLINE>
FT  30 MAY 92 / The Lex Column: South Africa
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
After enjoying a certain rehabilitation in world bond markets, South Africa
is turning its attention to international equities too. The forthcoming
Dollars 250m issue by Sappi, the paper concern, in theory offers an
opportunity to capitalise on South Africa's low-cost base as well as the
expected upturn in this sector.
That said, Sappi needs another two or three years to digest its recent
purchase of Germany's Hannover Papier. The political risk attached to South
Africa remains considerable. If its prospects are really that good, such a
low-geared company might be better off adding to its debt at this stage in
the cycle.
</TEXT>
