<HEADLINE>
FT  30 MAY 92 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Producer prices for spices remained unchanged as European grinders
maintained hand-to-mouth buying, reports Man Producten. But since prices for
some varieties were at historically low levels, buyers were showing more
interest in covering forward requirements. Vietnamese cassia, broken, was
quoted at USDollars 1,900 a tonne, cif, for June/July shipment, while
Seychelles supplies were on offer at Dollars 1,350, cif, Europe and
Madagascan cinnamom at FFr6.50 a kg, cif, for June/july shipment. Indonesian
cassia prices were unchanged. Cloves, remain cheap, with spot Madagascan at
Dollars 1,000 a tonne.
