FT  29 MAY 92 / International Company News: Good quarter for Magna
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
HIGHER North American car production and lower interest rates helped Magna
International, Canada's biggest independent car and parts maker, to achieve
a fourfold jump in third-quarter profits. The surge came on a 27.5 per cent
gain in sales.
Net profit was CDollars 30.5m (USDollars 25.40m), or 89 cents a share, for
the April 30 quarter, up from CDollars 4.4m, or 16 cents, a year earlier.
Sales were CDollars 632m against CDollars 495m.
Nine months' earnings amounted to CDollars 66.7m, or CDollars 2.13 a share,
against CDollars 4.9m, or 18 cents a year earlier, on sales of CDollars
1.7bn against CDollars 1.5bn.
