FT  29 MAY 92 / Pounds 200m bill for technology
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BUSINESS faces a Pounds 200m bill for technology needed to cope with new
Customs regulations in the single European market, according to research by
KPMG Peat Marwick, the accountancy group. Companies will have to provide
more detailed information when Customs entry documents are abolished from
the end of the year. KPMG says few companies in Britain have computer
systems capable of dealing with the new regulations. Changes to provide the
information needed by Customs and Excise would cost Pounds 200m.
